column_names: I can translate all 247 headers, but I need a formatting preference before I proceed.
How should I format the translations?
- Option A: snake_case with German words (und with umlauts ASCII-ized, e.g., bevoelkerung)
- Option B: natural German phrases with spaces (proper capitalization)
Also, how should I handle ambiguous cases like geo_id, geoidsl, geoidsc and some of the longer compound column names?
- Keep them as Geoid_SL / Geoid_SC (or Geoidsl / Geoidsc) or translate to Geoid-Identifikator variants?
- For umlauts, would you prefer ASCII-ized forms (Bevoelkerung) or proper umlaut characters (Bevölkerung)?
Tell me your preferred format, and I’ll produce exactly one translated line per input in that style.
